 {"id":"frankenjax-ta7n","title":"Default vmap pad interior padding in BatchTrace","description":"BatchTrace pad batching currently requires padding_interior even though fj-lax eval and fj-trace shape inference default omitted interior padding to zero. Add default handling and regression coverage so vmap over pad preserves the scoped API contract.","status":"closed","priority":2,"issue_type":"task","created_at":"2026-04-27T13:42:13.708180551Z","created_by":"ubuntu","updated_at":"2026-04-27T13:46:45.821030989Z","closed_at":"2026-04-27T13:46:45.819098128Z","close_reason":"Defaulted omitted BatchTrace pad interior padding to zero and added vmap regression coverage.","source_repo":".","compaction_level":0,"original_size":0}
+{"id":"frankenjax-tb5k","title":"Bound batched fixture timeout thread fan-out","description":"The fj-conformance batched transform fixture runner in crates/fj-conformance/src/lib.rs currently clones the entire bundle, spawns one OS thread per case up front, and then waits on each receiver with a timeout. Large oracle bundles can therefore create hundreds of threads immediately, and timed-out cases keep running in detached background threads. Change run_transform_fixture_bundle_batched so it starts each case only when it is being waited on and joins successful case threads after receiving their result, preserving report order while preventing all cases from fanning out at once. Add regression coverage with multiple delayed cases to prove timeout reporting still preserves case order. Validate with rch cargo test -p fj-conformance test_batch_runner, rch cargo check -p fj-conformance --all-targets, rch cargo clippy -p fj-conformance --all-targets -- -D warnings, cargo fmt --check, and ubs on the touched file.","status":"closed","priority":2,"issue_type":"bug","created_at":"2026-04-28T20:56:05.148998336Z","created_by":"ubuntu","updated_at":"2026-04-28T21:22:19.920118990Z","closed_at":"2026-04-28T21:22:19.918138058Z","close_reason":"Changed the batched transform fixture runner to start each case only when waiting on it, join completed worker threads, retain timeout reporting order, and added delayed-plus-fast regression coverage. Validated fmt, UBS, targeted fj-conformance test, fj-conformance check/clippy, and full workspace tests via rch.","source_repo":".","compaction_level":0,"original_size":0}
 {"id":"frankenjax-thk","title":"Align switch AD index semantics","description":"Port LAX switch scalar-index behavior into AD JVP/VJP: bool and scalar-tensor indices should select the matching branch, invalid/out-of-range indices should fail instead of silently routing gradients to branch 0.","status":"closed","priority":2,"issue_type":"task","created_at":"2026-04-27T11:26:38.158187964Z","created_by":"ubuntu","updated_at":"2026-04-27T11:37:28.425480815Z","closed_at":"2026-04-27T11:37:28.423513699Z","close_reason":"Aligned switch AD JVP/VJP index semantics with LAX for bool, scalar-tensor, branch-count, and invalid-index behavior.","source_repo":".","compaction_level":0,"original_size":0}
 {"id":"frankenjax-tr5","title":"Expand RNG distribution families: gamma, exponential, truncated normal, multi-key splitting","status":"closed","priority":2,"issue_type":"task","created_at":"2026-04-01T17:17:28.096697796Z","created_by":"ubuntu","updated_at":"2026-04-01T17:46:12.361420708Z","closed_at":"2026-04-01T17:46:12.361160305Z","close_reason":"Added 13 RNG distribution tests: multi-level split independence, multi-level split determinism, fold_in composition non-commutativity, fold_in sequence independence, large seed values (u64::MAX), exponential distribution via -log(uniform), truncated normal via rejection, multi-seed KS uniform (5 seeds), multi-seed normal stats (5 seeds), split samples uncorrelation (Pearson r). All 34 threefry tests pass.","source_repo":".","compaction_level":0,"original_size":0}
 {"id":"frankenjax-tu77","title":"Preserve F32 literals in AD zero/one helpers","description":"fj-ad zeros_like/ones_like still widen scalar and tensor F32 tangents to F64 even though native F32 literal parity is present elsewhere. Preserve F32Bits and F32 tensor dtype for zero/one tangent seeds where the helper mirrors the primal dtype, add focused JVP/zero-gradient tests, and validate fj-ad plus workspace gates.","status":"closed","priority":2,"issue_type":"bug","created_at":"2026-04-28T20:49:50.654696815Z","created_by":"ubuntu","updated_at":"2026-04-28T21:05:54.983456068Z","closed_at":"2026-04-28T21:05:54.981647860Z","close_reason":"Preserved F32Bits/F32 tensor width in fj-ad zero/one helpers; added helper and JVP floor F32 regression coverage; validated fmt, UBS, fj-ad tests, workspace check, and workspace clippy.","source_repo":".","compaction_level":0,"original_size":0}
